solution:
The circumference of the whole circle is $2 \pi \cdot 6 = 12 \pi$, so the circumference of the base of the cone is $12 \pi/3 = 4 \pi$.  Hence, the radius of the base of the cone is $4 \pi/(2 \pi) = 2$.

